<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-15T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-15T06:00:00-05:00" n="1081" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1081">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.00/213: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-15T13:00:00+02:00">November
                                    15, 1943—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 16—8:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2095. My 2086, November 15, 1 p.m. In absence of King from Cairo I
                            communicated to him today through the First Chamberlain <pb facs="1045" n="1033" xml:id="pg_1033"/> the same information regarding the
                            attitude of the American Government on the Lebanese crisis which I
                            conveyed to Nahas Pasha last night.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>